# Prisma Patterns

## Schema conventions
- Table names: `snake_case` via `@@map("table_name")`
- Model names: `PascalCase`
- Always include `createdAt DateTime @default(now())` and `updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt`
- Use enums for fixed value sets — never bare strings for status/type fields
- Add `@@index` for every field used in `WHERE` or `ORDER BY` clauses

## Service patterns

### Always inject PrismaService
```ts
constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}
```

### Prefer typed model methods
```ts
// ✅ correct
await this.prisma.scenarioRun.create({ data: { ... } });

// ❌ forbidden
await this.prisma.$queryRaw`SELECT * FROM scenario_runs`;
```

### Update pattern — always use `where: { id }` not `updateMany`
```ts
await this.prisma.scenarioRun.update({
  where: { id: run.id },
  data: { status: 'completed', duration },
});
```

### History queries — always paginate
```ts
await this.prisma.scenarioRun.findMany({
  orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },
  take: 20,
});
```

## Migrations
- Never edit migration SQL files after they are committed
- Always run `npm run prisma:migrate:dev` (from apps/backend) to create new migrations
- Migration name format: `<timestamp>_<snake_case_description>`
- `prisma migrate deploy` runs automatically on container start — do not call it manually

## Forbidden
- `$queryRaw` / `$executeRaw` — use model methods
- `prisma.$transaction` with raw SQL
- Importing `PrismaClient` directly — always use the injected `PrismaService`
- Modifying `@prisma/client` generated types — extend via DTOs instead
